                        <p>
                            Situated near the Persian Gulf on the Arabian Peninsula lies the small but strategically important country of Qatar. The country’s government is generally friendly toward the United States as well as several other countries (such as the United Kingdom and Saudi Arabia) and has allowed the U.S. and its allies to use its airspace and some air bases as they carry out missions in Iraq and Afghanistan.
